[Welcome to Wikipedia](/Help:Introduction)! This page lists some locations where you can ask questions or make comments . Once you have chosen an appropriate place to ask your question, follow the instructions on how to post your question. A helpful volunteer will answer your question shortly. Please note that misplaced questions may not be answered quickly.

See the [request directory](/Wikipedia:Request_directory) for a comprehensive directory of interactive services and assistance that can be requested on Wikipedia.



Comments about specific articles

• Each article has its own [talk page](/Wikipedia:Talk_page_guidelines) to ask questions or make constructive comments regarding its content, when you're viewing the article, just click on the Talk tab at the top of the page. Bear in mind, however, that [Wikipedia is not a forum for discussion](/Wikipedia:What_Wikipedia_is_not) about the topics of articles – comments should be limited to the article's content.

Questions about using and contributing to Wikipedia

Your question might have already been answered in the [frequently asked questions](/Wikipedia:FAQ/Index). Otherwise:

• [Your mentor](/Special:Homepage) is an experienced volunteer ready to help you with all your Wikipedia questions. You can contact them via [your Homepage](/Special:Homepage).

• [The Teahouse](/Wikipedia:Teahouse) is a friendly space for new editors to ask questions with answers from experienced editors.

• [The help desk](/Wikipedia:Help_desk) is the main place for asking questions and also where to turn when all else fails.

• [The village pump](/Wikipedia:Village_pump) is the forum for discussion of Wikipedia's more complex project-wide technical issues, policies, proposals, and operations.

• [Media copyright questions](/Wikipedia:Media_copyright_questions) covers the use of images and other media on Wikipedia.

Live chat help

• For assistance with Wikipedia-related queries (not general factual questions), you can join the [#wikipedia-en-help](/Wikipedia:IRC_help_disclaimer) IRC [chat room](/Chat_room) for live assistance.

Personal help on your talk page

• Click here to ask for help on your talk page ; a volunteer will visit you there. Otherwise, write {{[Help me](/Template:Help_me)}} and your question on a talk page (preferably [your own talk page](/Special:MyTalk)) and a volunteer will assist you there.

• If your request specifically requires [administrator](/Wikipedia:Administrators) assistance, place {{[Admin help](/Template:Admin_help)}} on [your talk page](/Special:MyTalk).

Factual questions

• The [reference desk](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk) is like a [library reference desk](/Reference_desk) where you can ask questions about any topic, except Wikipedia itself. The editors there will try to answer your questions or point you in the direction of the information you need.


e.g. "What country has the world's largest fishing fleet?"

The reference desk is divided into several subject areas:
[Computing](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk/Computing) – [Entertainment](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk/Entertainment) – [Language](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk/Language) – [Humanities](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk/Humanities) – [Mathematics](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk/Mathematics) – [Science](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk/Science)
If you're unsure of the exact area, use [Miscellaneous](/Wikipedia:Reference_desk/Miscellaneous) .

Contact Wikipedia

• [Contact us](/Wikipedia:Contact_us) is a page that describes how and where to contact Wikipedia directly for a variety of reasons.



